Incident: Possible SQL injection detected

Indicators:
Alert Trigger Reason : Requested URL Contains OR 1 = 1 
Source IP: 167.99.169.17
Source port: 49575
Destination IP: 172.16.17.18
Destination Port: 443

Investigation:
Understanding why alert was triggered:
  HTTP Request contained common SQL injection characters (OR 1 = 1)

Traffic information:
SOURCE:
  After researching ip address using ARIN Whois/RDAP, The IP address is owned by DigitalOcean.

DESTINATION:
The destination is a webserver on the simulated SIEM.

PROTOCAL
The protocal being used: HTTPS

Findings:
Someone using DigitalOcean cloud services attempted to execute SQL injection.

This user is not on the company network.

After decoding the https request: https://172.16.17.18/search/?q=" OR 1 = 1 -- -
This shows the attacker attempted to fill out a form with a query that is always true and comment out the rest. In conclusion this traffic is malicous.

Just to be sure, I analyzed the email logs to check if this was a scheduled test, it was not. Nothing like that was ever mentioned.

The traffic flow is Internet -> Company network.

After analysic the logs, the injection attempts all resulted in response code 500, which means server rejected, so the attack failed.

Conclusion:
True positive alert.

Response:
No escalation required.
